{"1":{"w":[{"b":"0.05","h":"0.85","c":"يَاأَيُّهَا","d":"yʾَٰٓayَhُّāَ","e":"yāayyuhā"},{"b":"2.6","h":"3.25","c":"النَّبِيُّ","d":"lٱnbَّàُِّ","e":"l-nabiyu"},{"b":"4.1","h":"4.65","c":"إِذَا","d":"ʾidِhāَ","e":"idhā"},{"b":"4.5","h":"5.2","c":"طَلَّقْتُمُ","d":"ṭlَqَّtْmُُ","e":"ṭallaqtumu"},{"b":"5.7","h":"6.59","c":"النِّسَاءَ","d":"lٱnsِّāَءَٓ","e":"l-nisāa"},{"b":"8.5","h":"9.08","c":"فَطَلِّقُوهُنَّ","d":"fṭَlَqِّwُhnَُّ","e":"faṭalliqūhunna"},{"b":"10.7","h":"11.5","c":"لِعِدَّتِهِنَّ","d":"lعِʿdِtَّhِnَِّ","e":"liʿiddatihinna"},{"b":"13.0","h":"13.72","c":"وَأَحْصُوا","d":"wʾَaḥَṣْwُā۟","e":"wa-aḥṣū"},{"b":"13.8","h":"14.59","c":"الْعِدَّةَ","d":"lٱعْʿdِẗََّ","e":"l-ʿidata"},{"b":"15.3","h":"18.5","c":"وَاتَّقُوا","d":"wtٱَqَّwُā۟","e":"wa-ittaqū"},{"b":"16.0","h":"19.33","c":"اللَّهَ","d":"lٱlhََّ","e":"l-laha"},{"b":"16.6","h":"20.11","c":"رَبَّكُمْ","d":"rbَkَّmُْ","e":"rabbakum"},{"b":"18.1","h":"22.7","c":"لَا","d":"lāَ","e":"lā"},{"b":"18.4","h":"23.07","c":"تُخْرِجُوهُنَّ","d":"tkُhrْgِjwُhnَُّ","e":"tukh'rijūhunna"},{"b":"20.6","h":"25.47","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِۢ","e":"min"},{"b":"21.6","h":"26.44","c":"بُيُوتِهِنَّ","d":"byُwُthِnَِّ","e":"buyūtihinna"},{"b":"23.6","h":"28.5","c":"وَلَا","d":"wlَāَ","e":"walā"},{"b":"24.1","h":"29.18","c":"يَخْرُجْنَ","d":"ykَhrْgُjnَْ","e":"yakhruj'na"},{"b":"25.1","h":"30.31","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ʾilِāَّٓ","e":"illā"},{"b":"28.9","h":"32.26","c":"أَنْ","d":"ʾanَ","e":"an"},{"b":"30.9","h":"33.48","c":"يَأْتِينَ","d":"yʾَatْyِnَ","e":"yatīna"},{"b":"31.7","h":"34.62","c":"بِفَاحِشَةٍ","d":"bfِḥَٰsِhẗٍَ","e":"bifāḥishatin"},{"b":"34.0","h":"37.03","c":"مُبَيِّنَةٍ","d":"mbُّyَnِّẗٍَ","e":"mubayyinatin"},{"b":"35.5","h":"41.19","c":"وَتِلْكَ","d":"wtَlِkَْ","e":"watil'ka"},{"b":"36.2","h":"42.02","c":"حُدُودُ","d":"ḥdُwُdُ","e":"ḥudūdu"},{"b":"37.1","h":"43.22","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"lٱlhَِّ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"39.9","h":"46.6","c":"وَمَنْ","d":"wmَnَ","e":"waman"},{"b":"40.9","h":"47.57","c":"يَتَعَدَّ","d":"ytَعَʿdََّ","e":"yataʿadda"},{"b":"41.7","h":"48.74","c":"حُدُودَ","d":"ḥdُwُdَ","e":"ḥudūda"},{"b":"42.5","h":"49.79","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"lٱlhَِّ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"43.","h":"50.78","c":"فَقَدْ","d":"fqَdَْ","e":"faqad"},{"b":"43.8","h":"51.43","c":"ظَلَمَ","d":"ẓlَmََ","e":"ẓalama"},{"b":"44.","h":"52.37","c":"نَفْسَهُ","d":"nfَsْhَۥُ","e":"nafsahu"},{"b":"45.7","h":"54.95","c":"لَا","d":"lāَ","e":"lā"},{"b":"46.","h":"55.33","c":"تَدْرِي","d":"tdَrْàِ","e":"tadrī"},{"b":"46.9","h":"56.4","c":"لَعَلَّ","d":"lعَʿlََّ","e":"laʿalla"},{"b":"47.6","h":"57.36","c":"اللَّهَ","d":"lٱlhََّ","e":"l-laha"},{"b":"48.3","h":"58.46","c":"يُحْدِثُ","d":"yḥُdْtِhُ","e":"yuḥ'dithu"},{"b":"49.1","h":"59.48","c":"بَعْدَ","d":"bعَʿdَْ","e":"baʿda"},{"b":"49.","h":"60.21","c":"ذَلِكَ","d":"dhlَٰkَِ","e":"dhālika"},{"b":"50.2","h":"61.43","c":"أَمْرًا","d":"ʾamَrْāً","e":"amran"}],"a":{"g":"O Prophet, when you [Muslims] divorce women, divorce them for [the commencement of] their waiting period and keep count of the waiting period, and fear Allah, your Lord. Do not turn them out of their [husbands'] houses, nor should they [themselves] leave [during that period] unless they are committing a clear immorality. And those are the limits [set by] Allah. And whoever transgresses the limits of Allah has certainly wronged himself. You know not; perhaps Allah will bring about after that a [different] matter.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولأن أصول هذه المعانى لا تختلف فيها الشرائع وإنما تختلف في وجوه التحديد كما يحد شرع عيسى ابن مريم عليه السلام تحريم الخمر بالسكر وقد حده شرعنا بكونه من جنس المسكر لأن قليله يدعو إلى كثير والداخل في الحدود داخل في التحريم بحكم الجنس كما دخل أصل المعنى بالجملة الأصلية فهذا مثال واحد لحكمه خفية من حكم النقدين فينبغى أن يعتبر شكر النعمة وكفرانها بهذا المثال فكل ما خلق لحكمة فينبغى أن يصرف عنها ولا يعرف هذا إلا من قد عرف الحكمة - ومن يؤت الحكمة فقد أوتي خيرا كثيرا - ولكن لا تصادف جواهر الحكم في قلوب هى مزابل الشهوات وملاعب الشياطين بل لا يتذكر إلا أولوا الألباب ولذلك قال ﭬ: (لولا أن الشياطين يحومون على قلوب بنى آدم لنظروا إلى ملكوت السماء[53])\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, the foundations [usul] of these meanings [ma'ani] do not differ among the divine laws [shara'i'], but they differ only in the aspects of definition [tahdid]. Just as the law [shar'] of Jesus, son of Mary, peace be upon him, defined the prohibition of wine [khamr] by intoxication [sukr], and our law [shar'] defined it by its being of the intoxicating kind [jins al-musakkar], because a little of it leads to much. And what falls within the definitions falls within the prohibition by the ruling of the kind [hukm al-jins], just as the root meaning [asl al-ma'na] entered by the foundational totality [al-jumla al-asliyya]. This is but one example of its hidden ruling [hukm khafiy] from the ruling of the two standards [al-naqdayn].\n\nTherefore, one should consider gratitude [shukr] for blessing [ni'ma] and ingratitude [kufran] for it by this example. For everything created for a wisdom [hikma] should be directed toward it, and none knows this except he who has known the wisdom [hikma]—\"And whoever is given wisdom [hikma] has been given much good\"—but the essences [jawahir] of the wisdoms [hikam] do not befall hearts [qulub] that are refuse dumps [mazabil] for lusts [shahawat] and playgrounds [mala'ib] for devils [shayatin]. Rather, none take heed [yatadhakkar] except those of understanding [ulu al-albab]. And for that reason He, exalted is He, said: \"If it were not that the devils [shayatin] hover around the hearts [qulub] of the children of Adam, they would gaze upon the kingdom [malakut] of the heavens.\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"فَإِذَا","d":"fʾَidِhāَ","e":"fa-idhā"},{"b":"0.69","h":"1.13","c":"بَلَغْنَ","d":"blَغَnَْ","e":"balaghna"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.13","c":"أَجَلَهُنَّ","d":"ʾagَjlَhَnَُّ","e":"ajalahunna"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.16","c":"فَأَمْسِكُوهُنَّ","d":"fʾَamَsْkِwُhnَُّ","e":"fa-amsikūhunna"},{"b":"5.1","h":"7.22","c":"بِمَعْرُوفٍ","d":"bmِعَʿrْwُfٍ","e":"bimaʿrūfin"},{"b":"6.4","h":"9.18","c":"أَوْ","d":"ʾawَْ","e":"aw"},{"b":"6.7","h":"9.7","c":"فَارِقُوهُنَّ","d":"fāَrqِwُhnَُّ","e":"fāriqūhunna"},{"b":"8.8","h":"12.56","c":"بِمَعْرُوفٍ","d":"bmِعَʿrْwُfٍ","e":"bimaʿrūfin"},{"b":"10.","h":"15.1","c":"وَأَشْهِدُوا","d":"wʾَasَhhْdِwُā۟","e":"wa-ashhidū"},{"b":"11.9","h":"16.71","c":"ذَوَيْ","d":"dhwَàَْ","e":"dhaway"},{"b":"12.4","h":"17.48","c":"عَدْلٍ","d":"عʿdَlٍْ","e":"ʿadlin"},{"b":"13.8","h":"19.2","c":"مِنْكُمْ","d":"mnِّkmُْ","e":"minkum"},{"b":"15.2","h":"21.12","c":"وَأَقِيمُوا","d":"wʾَaqَyِmwُā۟","e":"wa-aqīmū"},{"b":"16.1","h":"22.61","c":"الشَّهَادَةَ","d":"lٱshhَّdَٰẗََ","e":"l-shahādata"},{"b":"18","h":"24.48","c":"لِلَّهِ","d":"llِhَِّ","e":"lillahi"},{"b":"20.0","h":"29.65","c":"ذَلِكُمْ","d":"dhlَٰkِmُْ","e":"dhālikum"},{"b":"21.0","h":"31.01","c":"يُوعَظُ","d":"ywُعʿẓَُ","e":"yūʿaẓu"},{"b":"21.","h":"32.31","c":"بِهِ","d":"bhِۦِ","e":"bihi"},{"b":"22.3","h":"33.21","c":"مَنْ","d":"mnَ","e":"man"},{"b":"23.3","h":"34.27","c":"كَانَ","d":"kāَnَ","e":"kāna"},{"b":"23.9","h":"35.18","c":"يُؤْمِنُ","d":"yʾُwmْnُِ","e":"yu'minu"},{"b":"24.7","h":"36.27","c":"بِاللَّهِ","d":"blٱِlhَِّ","e":"bil-lahi"},{"b":"25.7","h":"37.68","c":"وَالْيَوْمِ","d":"wlٱَyْwَmِْ","e":"wal-yawmi"},{"b":"26.6","h":"39.1","c":"الْءَاخِرِ","d":"lٱءْāَkhrِِ","e":"l-ākhiri"},{"b":"28.1","h":"42.02","c":"وَمَنْ","d":"wmَnَ","e":"waman"},{"b":"29.5","h":"43.36","c":"يَتَّقِ","d":"ytَqَِّ","e":"yattaqi"},{"b":"30.1","h":"44.64","c":"اللَّهَ","d":"lٱlhََّ","e":"l-laha"},{"b":"30.","h":"45.78","c":"يَجْعَلْ","d":"ygَjعْʿlَ","e":"yajʿal"},{"b":"31.8","h":"46.64","c":"لَهُ","d":"lhَّۥُ","e":"lahu"},{"b":"32.3","h":"47.91","c":"مَخْرَجًا","d":"mkَhrْgَjāً","e":"makhrajan"}],"a":{"g":"And when they have [nearly] fulfilled their term, either retain them according to acceptable terms or part with them according to acceptable terms. And bring to witness two just men from among you and establish the testimony for [the acceptance of] Allah. That is instructed to whoever should believe in Allah and the Last day. And whoever fears Allah - He will make for him a way out","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                فإن اشتغلت بالتقوى شاهدت بالتجربة مصداق قوله تعالى: \" ومن يتق الله يجعل له مخرجاً ويرزقه من حيث لا يحتسب \" الآية، إلا أنه لم يتكفل له أن يرزقه لحم الطير ولذائذ الأطعمة، فما ضمن إلا الرزق الذي تدوم به حياته، وهذا المضمون مبذول كل من اشتغل بالضامن واطمأن إلى ضمانه؛ فإن الذي أحاط به تدبير الله من الأسباب الخفية للرزق أعظم مما ظهر للخلق، بل مداخل الرزق لا تحصى ومجاريه لا يهتدى إليها، وذلك لأن ظهوره على الأرض وسببه في السماء\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, if you occupy yourself with God-consciousness [taqwa], you will witness through direct experience the truth of His saying, the Most High: \"And whoever is conscious of God, He will make for him a way out, and will provide for him from where he does not expect\" (65:2-3). However, He has not guaranteed for him that He will provide him with the meat of birds and the delights of foods. He has only guaranteed the provision [rizq] by which his life is sustained, and this guarantee is granted to everyone who occupies himself with the Guarantor and is content with His guarantee. For the hidden means [asbab] of provision [rizq] with which God's management [tadbir] has encompassed him are greater than what has become apparent to creation. Nay, the avenues of provision [rizq] cannot be enumerated, and its channels cannot be discovered. This is because its manifestation is on the earth, while its cause [sabab] is in the heaven.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"وَيَرْزُقْهُ","d":"wyَrَzْqُhُْ","e":"wayarzuq'hu"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.89","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِْ","e":"min"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.37","c":"حَيْثُ","d":"ḥyَtْhُ","e":"ḥaythu"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.41","c":"لَا","d":"lāَ","e":"lā"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.07","c":"يَحْتَسِبُ","d":"yḥَtْsَbُِ","e":"yaḥtasibu"},{"b":"3.8","h":"7.2","c":"وَمَنْ","d":"wmَnَ","e":"waman"},{"b":"5.1","h":"8.59","c":"يَتَوَكَّلْ","d":"ytَwَkَlَّْ","e":"yatawakkal"},{"b":"6.0","h":"10.14","c":"عَلَى","d":"عʿlَàَ","e":"ʿalā"},{"b":"6.6","h":"10.82","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"lٱlhَِّ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"7.3","h":"12.13","c":"فَهُوَ","d":"fhَwَُ","e":"fahuwa"},{"b":"7.9","h":"13.06","c":"حَسْبُهُ","d":"ḥsَbْhُۥُٓ","e":"ḥasbuhu"},{"b":"9.1","h":"15.7","c":"إِنَّ","d":"ʾinَِّ","e":"inna"},{"b":"10.4","h":"17.08","c":"اللَّهَ","d":"lٱlhََّ","e":"l-laha"},{"b":"11.2","h":"18.42","c":"بَالِغُ","d":"blَٰغُِ","e":"bālighu"},{"b":"12.1","h":"19.63","c":"أَمْرِهِ","d":"ʾamَrْhِۦِ","e":"amrihi"},{"b":"13.1","h":"22.1","c":"قَدْ","d":"qdَْ","e":"qad"},{"b":"13.4","h":"22.49","c":"جَعَلَ","d":"gjعَʿlََ","e":"jaʿala"},{"b":"14.0","h":"23.38","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"lٱlhَُّ","e":"l-lahu"},{"b":"14.8","h":"24.77","c":"لِكُلِّ","d":"lkِlُِّ","e":"likulli"},{"b":"15.6","h":"25.93","c":"شَيْءٍ","d":"shàَءٍْ","e":"shayin"},{"b":"17.3","h":"27.93","c":"قَدْرًا","d":"qdَrْāً","e":"qadran"}],"a":{"g":"And will provide for him from where he does not expect. And whoever relies upon Allah - then He is sufficient for him. Indeed, Allah will accomplish His purpose. Allah has already set for everything a [decreed] extent.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال تعالى: \" ومن يتوكل على الله فهو حسبه \". وأعظم بمقام موسوم بمحبة الله تعالى صاحبه، ومضمون كفاية الله تعالى ملابسه، فمن الله تعالى حسبه وكافيه ومحبه ومراعيه: فقد فاز الفوز العظيم، فإن المحبوب لا يعذب ولا يبعد ولا يحجب.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, and He, the Exalted, said: \"And whoever relies upon Allah, then He is sufficient for him.\" And how great is a station [maqam] characterized by the love [mahabbah] of Allah, the Exalted, its possessor, and guaranteed by the sufficiency [kifayah] of Allah, the Exalted, its companion. So for whom Allah, the Exalted, is his Sufficiency [hasbuh] and his Provider [kafih] and his Beloved [muhibbuh] and his Guardian [mura'ih]: he has attained the supreme success [al-fawz al-'azim]. For the beloved [mahbub] is not punished, nor distanced, nor veiled [mahjub].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"4":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"وَاللَّائِي","d":"wlٱَـَّٰٓàِٔ","e":"wa-allāī"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.2","c":"يَئِسْنَ","d":"yʾَysِnَْ","e":"ya-is'na"},{"b":"3.1","h":"4.37","c":"مِنَ","d":"mnَِ","e":"mina"},{"b":"3.4","h":"4.94","c":"الْمَحِيضِ","d":"lٱmْḥَyِḍِ","e":"l-maḥīḍi"},{"b":"4.5","h":"6.61","c":"مِنْ","d":"mnِ","e":"min"},{"b":"5.5","h":"7.69","c":"نِسَائِكُمْ","d":"nsِّāَʾٓy